    "content": "Balin's Post is a small trade hub on the Kingsroad. The following shops and merchants are common within the bustling township:\r\n\r\nApothecary: \r\n\r\nThe Old Maple Tavern\r\nTwo Snakes Inn\r\n\r\nWeaponsmith: The Pointy End\r\n\r\nArmorsmith: Corvin's Heavy-Ass Armor and Big-Ass Shields\r\n\r\nGeneral Store: Bartholomew's Bargain Basement\r\n\r\nThe Wayfarer's - Couriers and mailcarriers. Three jobs potentially:\r\n\r\nClothier - Dapper Dullahan \r\n\r\nTriplets: butcher, baker, candlestick maker\r\nJones, James, and Jimmy have all had a falling out \r\n\r\nThe Mirage: Exotic Goods\r\n\r\nDirty  Larry: A guy down by the wharf who'll buy anything, but refuses to deal in gold directly. Strictly items for trade.\r\n\r\nFabled Findings: Magic Shop\r\n- Common Spell Scrolls\r\n- 1x Scroll of Identify\r\n- 2x Greater Healing Potions\r\n- Charlatan's Die, (requires attunement) Whenever you roll this six-sided die, you can control which number it rolls.\r\n- Feather Token (Feather Fall) This small metal disk is inscribed with the image of a feather. When you fall at least 20 feet while the token is on your person, you descend 60 feet per round and take no damage from falling. The token’s magic is expended after you land, whereupon the disk becomes nonmagical.\r\n- Instrument of Illusions, while you are playing this musical instrument, you can take a Magic action to create harmless, illusory visual effects within a 5-foot Emanation originating from the instrument. If you are a Bard, the size of the Emanation increases to 15 feet. Sample visual effects include luminous musical notes, a spectral dancer, butterflies, and gently falling snow. The magical effects have neither substance nor sound, and they are obviously illusory.\r\n- Bag of Holding\r\n- Potion of Pugilism\r\n- Glowrune Pigment",
